the key characters of ethics 

## Transparency

When AI makes a decision that affects your life, 
like whether you get a loan or a job interview, 
you deserve to know why. 
Right now a lot of AI works like a black box. 
Something goes in, something comes out, and nobody really knows what happened in the middle. 
That is a problem and it needs to be fixed.

## Fairness and Bias

AI learns from data made by humans and humans have always had biases. 
So if you train an AI on old hiring records from a company that mostly hired men, 
the AI might start preferring men too without anyone telling it to. 
This kind of thing has already happened in real life and it is something people are actively working to fix.

## Privacy

AI needs massive amounts of information to learn and a lot of that information is about real people, 
sometimes without them even knowing. Every time you use an app, search something, or walk past a camera, you might be feeding an AI somewhere. 
The question of who owns that data and what they can do with it is still being argued over by governments and companies right now.

## Accountability

If an AI makes a mistake that hurts someone, who is to blame? The person who built it? The company that sold it? The person who used it? Right now the answer is often nobody, 
which is obviously not good enough. We need clear rules about who is responsible before more people get hurt.

